7.1.2 - M365SR02: Unrestricted Geographic and Network Access
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1563; Revision: 0; Updated: Sep-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Restricting access to cloud services based on risk)
•	Control: 0957; Revision: 7; Updated: Sep-23; Applicability: All; OS: All (Restricting access to systems and applications)
•	Control: 1506; Revision: 1; Updated: Jun-21; Applicability: All; OS: All (Evaluation of cloud service security)
________________________________________
Current Risk
Without geographic and IP address restrictions applied to the agency’s Azure and M365 tenancy, the cloud SaaS platform is accessible globally, leading to an increased attack surface and higher likelihood of an Azure/M365 account compromise, resulting in the compromise of confidentiality, availability and integrity of agency systems, data and/or information.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
POSSIBLE	x	MAJOR	=	HIGH
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Implement Geofencing: Configure Entra ID Conditional Access policies to block authentication attempts from all countries except Australia and approved international jurisdictions.
2.	Enforce Trusted Network Locations: Define and mandate the use of agency-controlled IP ranges for high-privilege administrative tasks and sensitive data access.
3.	Deploy Sign-in Risk Policies: Integrate Entra ID Identity Protection to automatically block or require MFA for sign-ins originating from anonymous IP addresses or atypical locations.
- Treatment #1
•	Define Named Locations: Identify and document the agency’s trusted egress IP addresses and required geographic regions for remote staff.
•	Configure Conditional Access (CA): Develop and test CA policies that explicitly "Allow" access from Australia while "Blocking" all other regions by default.
•	Log Analysis and Alerting: Configure Azure Monitor to alert security operations (SecOps) when authentication attempts are blocked by geographic or IP-based restrictions.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
By restricting the logical boundaries of the tenancy to known-good geographic regions and IP ranges, the available attack surface for external threat actors is significantly reduced. This makes it substantially harder for credential-harvesting or brute-force attacks from foreign jurisdictions to succeed, lowering the likelihood to "Rare."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
RARE	x	MAJOR	=	MEDIUM

